thread.title: AREA COLLEGES: UCR women's soccer blanks Cal Poly

author: The Press-Enterprise
title: AREA COLLEGES: UCR women's soccer blanks Cal Poly
text:
NEWS SERVICE REPORTS
Published: Oct. 25, 2015 Updated: 9:58 p.m. Brittany Mata and Tyler Cunningham each scored a goal as UC Riverside blanked Cal Poly, 2-0, in a Big West women’s soccer match in San Luis Obispo on Sunday.
Mata scored in the ninth minute for the Highlanders (10-8-0 overall, 4-3-0 Big West), who are in fifth place with one conference match remaining. Cunningham added a goal four minutes into the second half.
Goalkeeper Elizabeth Silas had four saves for the shutout.
MORE WOMEN’S SOCCER
Cal State Monterey Bay 3, CSUSB 0: The Otters scored two goals in the first five minutes of the second half and took the decision over Cal State San Bernardino in a CCAA women’s soccer match in Seaside.
Regan Porteous scored her fifth goal of the year in the 47th minute, then assisted three minutes later on a goal by Kristen Womack of the Otters (6-10-1 overall, 3-7-1 CCAA). The Coyotes are 4-9-3, 3-6-1.
MEN’S SOCCER
Cal State Monterey Bay 1, CSUSB 0: Emmanuel Corona scored in the final minute of the first half, and the Otters (8-7, 5-6) defeated the visiting Coyotes in a CCAA match.
The Coyotes outshot the Otters 12-7. Goalkeeper Ivan Sanchez made three saves for CSUSB (3-8-3, 1-6-3).
WOMEN’S VOLLEYBALL
La Sierra def. Antelope Valley: Caitlin Marinos had 12 kills as the Golden Eagles (12-7 overall, 5-2 CalPac) won 25-21, 25-8, 25-18.
WOMEN’S CROSS COUNTRY
CSUSB places third at CCAA championships: Cal State San Bernardino senior Soleil Hall placed 11th in 21:56.5 for all-conference honors and helped pace the Coyotes to 100 points. Chico State placed first with 38 points while UC San Diego had 61.
Also scoring for the Coyotes were Laura Aceves (21st, 22:14.9), Patricia Cortez (29th, 22:24.8), Jessica Stienhoff (30th, 22:25.8) and Evelyn De La Luz (35th, 22:27.9).
Chico State’s McCall Hebermehl won the race in 21:33.1.
